node.text: We all remember where we were on 9/11.. The world came to a grinding halt. But for these brave women and their young children, that day left them wondering how they’d learn to carry on. And now, 20 years later, this new generation is writing its own story—their father’s legacies shining through them. Their stories of loss, resilience, and hope captured mine and Jo’s hearts, and we’re honored to bring this documentary to our network. You can watch “Rebuilding Hope: The Children of 9/11” on @discoveryplus. #MagnoliaNetwork #NeverForget

node.text: Jo and I met Bailey back in 2017, and seeing him now as a healthy young man reminds me why we were drawn to St. Jude™️. As if fighting diseases and cancer wasn’t impressive enough, families never receive a single bill. And I don’t know about you, but I think we ought to keep it that way. Click the button on my profile to donate to @stjude. #ChipInForStJude

node.text: We all remember where we were on 9/11.. The world came to a grinding halt. But for these brave women and their young children, that day left them wondering how they’d learn to carry on. And now, 20 years later, this new generation is writing its own story—their father’s legacies shining through them. Their stories of loss, resilience, and hope captured mine and Jo’s hearts, and we’re honored to bring this documentary to our network. You can watch “Rebuilding Hope: The Children of 9/11” on @discoveryplus. #MagnoliaNetwork #NeverForget

node.text: WOW.. turns out some of y’all really don’t like my hair!  But I can take it because I’ve been growing it out for a good reason. So now’s your chance to put your money where your mouth is.. I’m going to cut my hair, and I’m asking you to cut a check—and let’s see if we can raise a boatload of money for the kids at @stjude. The hair’s coming off on Friday, but between now and then, let’s chip in together for a good cause. And when it’s all said and done, I’ll donate my hair to @cwhl_org. Let's do this! #ChipInForStJude (link in profile)
